result.execSummary:
The defendant Gage A Timmer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: THE DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS SHALL DEDUCT RESTITUTION AND ALL OTHER COURT OBLIGATIONS AT THE RATE OF 25% OF ALL MONIES RECEIVED WHILE INCARCERATED.
If the defendant's probation is revoked, the conditions of extended supervision shall be the same as the conditions of probation.

miscConds.notes:
Pay $500.00 fine plus costs and Department of Corrections Supervision Fees.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
------------------------------

Restitution is set at $3,522.65, joint and several with co-actors, subject to defendant's right to challenge within 60 days.  Restitution is held open 60 days.
-------------------------------

No contact, direct or indirect, with the victim or her family other than in legal proceedings. Not to possess or consume alcohol. Not to possess any controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
------------------------------

Comply with low risk sex offender treatment.  Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent. Provide DNA Sample and pay surcharge. Maintain absolute sobriety. Any prescription medications to be made known to the Agent and taken as prescribed.
------------------------------
Court finds defendant EXEMPT from registering as a sex offender. This exemption was used under Statute 301.45.

timeConds.notes: to commence on or before March 28, 2015 @ 8:00 a.m. NOTE: The defendant is to serve the first three (3) months with NO work release and the second three (3) months are with work release and may be served on electronic monitoring if allowed by the Jail.
